  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Comparison of 2 hook-up protocols to perform home-based sleep studies in patients suspected
      of sleep-disordered breathing.

      First one: hook-up is performed in the hospital, around 4 PM, and the patient go home with
      the portable monitoring.

      Second one: hook-up is performed home, around 7 PM, and the patient has not to move after
      hook-up.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      All the patients will undergo 2 polysomnographies, according to two different hook-up
      protocols, within 2 weeks. Order of the exams will be randomized.

      We hypothesised that quality of recording is better when hook-up is performed at home.

      Final polysomnographic diagnosis, with the 2 different techniques, must be similar.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
